The paper focuses on improving the convergence of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) in a high-resolution setting, specifically for generating human faces. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new layered network structure and introduces a novel dataset, which are both related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions illumination conditions, which suggests that it may be related to Graphics (cs.GR) and Multimedia (cs.MM).
